current.title: Grotte [TRNR012]
current.about:
Parule makes his debut with his first EP „Grotte“. Dive deep into the realm of the weird and unknown with the first track, letting one get sucked into a dark space full of curiosity. 
Eyes still not adjusted to the darkness, „Blind Descend“ drags you further down the rabbit hole, with the unsettling feeling of not knowing what lies beyond.
„Lost in Translation“ manifests in driving conversations with the first encounter with what one would call something familiar. 
Finding common ground, the uneasy thoughts dissolve into a endless groove where one can „Dance with the Unknown“.
current.credits:
Produced by Paul Hammer
Mastered by Christopher Herb

current.title: It’s Not Over Till You’re Under//Ground [TRNR008]
current.about: "It's Not Over Till You're Under // Ground" is BYDL's debut EP. A collection of tracks which plunge into the depression of 2020 and seek hope where there seems to be no more. Dark synthesizers, distorted guitars and cutting dissonances characterize the INOTYUG EP. The four tracks describe a descent into the deepest feelings of a frayed time, dominated by distance and coldness. Rocking between pounding aggressiveness and gentle calming down – with a climax that addresses the absurdity of human conflict in the most extreme form of war. The EP can be understood as conceptual work that throws around references, codes and hidden meanings, but always remains vague enough to leave room for interpretation. The only thing that is stated as clearly as possible: This is anti-discriminatory music.
current.credits:
All Music Written and Recorded by Sandro Nicolussi in Vienna, 2020.
Fixing and Mixing: Raphael Fuchs (ø.FVCHS)
Mastering: Christopher Jan Herb (Akaroid)

current.title: Equinox [TRNR004]
current.about: For EQUINOX, the first in a new series of releases, Berlin-based artist AKAROID revolutionized his process to create music. Instead of arranging the songs on a computer, he performed and recorded them on a modular synthesizer each in one go – without any cuts or edits. What might appear counter-productive in the digital age, resulted in three performances that have a deeply natural flow to it. EQUINOX are pulsing soundscapes and melodies intertwined with banging syncopated beats. Funky but gefährlich.
current.credits:
Mixed and performed on modular synthesizers by Akaroid
Post-production by Erik Emil Eskildsen and Akaroid
Mastered by Akaroid

current.about: With his third EP release OMEGA, the Berlin-based artist AKAROID channeled intense and dark feelings into 3 rhythmically complex dance pieces whose encapsulating repetitiveness makes them impossible to escape from.

Mastered by Akaroid

current.title: Beta [TRNR002]
current.about: BETA, the second EP by Berlin based producer AKAROID, explores straight dance rhythms, structural arrangements and distorted bass sounds. Intricate chord structures and field recordings provide depth to the fast-forward thumping grooves, while bell-like lead tones counterpoint the warm undertone of the tracks. BETA is a futuristic journey; mysterious in nature but positive at heart.
current.credits:
Written and produced by Akaroid
Mastered by Akaroid

current.title: Omikron [TRNR001]
current.about: The debut EP 'OMIKRON' by Berlin based artist AKAROID, is a manifest of broken beats and intricate melodies. The arrangements root in complex songwriting but always maintain a danceability, which is deeply inspired by Berlin's diverse experimental techno scene. The EP opens with the playful, desiring track 'Infinities', followed by the unsettling, primal tones of 'Moving'. The breakbeat song 'Break 13' then releases you with dubby vibes and subtle poly rhythms which will make you yearn for more.
current.credits:
Written and produced by Akaroid
Mastered by Akaroid
